Java Conditional Statements Practice Questions (Basic → Advanced)

Practice these questions using if, if-else, else-if ladder, nested if, and switch statements.

🟢 Basic Level (1–10)
1. Check whether a number is positive or negative.
2. Check whether a number is even or odd.
3. Check whether a person is eligible to vote (age ≥ 18).
4. Find the greater of two numbers.
5. Find the smaller of two numbers.
6. Check whether a number is divisible by 5.
7. Check whether a number is divisible by both 3 and 7.
8. Check whether a character is uppercase or lowercase.
9. Check whether a character is a vowel or consonant.
10. Check whether a year is a leap year.
🟡 Intermediate Level (11–20)
11. Find the largest among three numbers.
12. Find the smallest among three numbers.
13. Check whether a number is a 2-digit, 3-digit, or 4-digit number.
14. Enter marks and print:
Distinction (≥75)
First Class (60–74)
Second Class (50–59)
Pass (35–49)
Fail (<35)
15. Check whether a number is positive, negative, or zero.
16. Find the absolute value of a number.
17. Check whether a character is an alphabet, digit, or special character.
18. Calculate electricity bill:
First 100 units: ₹5/unit
Next 100 units: ₹7/unit
Above 200 units: ₹10/unit
19. Calculate salary after adding bonus:
Salary > 50,000 → 20% bonus
Otherwise → 10% bonus
20. Find the maximum among four numbers.
🔴 Advanced Level (21–30)
21. Check whether a number is divisible by both 5 and 11.
22. Check whether three angles can form a triangle.
23. Check whether three sides form a valid triangle.
24. Find the type of triangle:
Equilateral
Isosceles
Scalene
25. Check whether a character is a vowel using switch.
26. Create a menu-driven calculator using switch:
Addition
Subtraction
Multiplication
Division
27. Print the day name using day number (1–7) with switch.
28. Print the month name using month number (1–12).
29. Find the largest among five numbers using nested if.
30. Calculate income tax:
Income ≤ ₹2,50,000 → No tax
₹2,50,001–₹5,00,000 → 5%
₹5,00,001–₹10,00,000 → 20%
Above ₹10,00,000 → 30%
🏆 Challenge Questions (31–40)
31. Check whether a number is a palindrome.
32. Check whether a number is an Armstrong number.
33. Check whether a number is a perfect number.
34. Check whether a number is prime.
35. Find the second largest among three numbers.
36. Find the largest among five numbers without using arrays.
37. Implement a simple ATM menu using switch.
38. Create a login system that validates username and password.
39. Build a grading system that also prints remarks:
A → Excellent
B → Good
C → Average
D → Needs Improvement
F → Fail
40. Create a restaurant menu using switch that displays the selected item's price.